theorem diff_frontier_eq_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    (A \ frontier A : Set X) = interior A := by
  classical
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hx
    have hxA : x ∈ A := hx.1
    have hNotFront : x ∉ frontier A := hx.2
    by_cases hInt : x ∈ interior A
    · exact hInt
    ·
      have hFront : x ∈ frontier A := by
        have h : x ∈ (closure A) \ interior A :=
          And.intro (subset_closure hxA) hInt
        simpa [frontier_eq_closure_diff_interior] using h
      exact (hNotFront hFront).elim
  · intro hxInt
    have hxA : x ∈ A := interior_subset hxInt
    have hNotFront : x ∉ frontier A := by
      intro hFront
      have h : x ∈ (closure A) \ interior A := by
        simpa [frontier_eq_closure_diff_interior] using hFront
      exact (h.2 hxInt)
    exact And.intro hxA hNotFront

theorem union_interior_closure_eq_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior A ∪ closure A = closure A := by
  -- `interior A` is always contained in `closure A`.
  have h_subset : (interior A : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
    intro x hx
    exact subset_closure hx
  -- Establish the desired set equality via extensionality.
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hx
    cases hx with
    | inl hxInt => exact h_subset hxInt
    | inr hxCl  => exact hxCl
  · intro hx
    exact Or.inr hx

theorem frontier_subset_closure_compl {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    frontier (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (Aᶜ) := by
  intro x hx
  -- Reinterpret `hx` using the characterization
  -- `frontier A = closure A ∩ closure (Aᶜ)`.
  have hx_inter : x ∈ closure A ∩ closure (Aᶜ) := by
    have h_eq :=
      (closure_inter_closure_compl_eq_frontier (X := X) (A := A)).symm
    simpa [h_eq] using hx
  -- Conclude with the second component of the intersection.
  exact hx_inter.2
